$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Hold on, Tingko...
Tingko: What? You're not used to wearing this kind of stuff?
Tindoiimu: Um, I don't know if that's really the point...
Tindoiimu: Just... isn't it kind of weird for me to wear men's clothing? I mean, wearing a disguise is fine and all, but why do I have to be a man?
Tingko: Because doing this is way more fu—
Tingko: I mean... uh... this kind of clothing suits you, Sir~
Tingko: Come on, I spent days working on this~!
Tindoiimu: Does it really suit me?
Tingko: It does! I measured everything and customized this just for you!
Tingko: The clerk didn't bat an eye just now when we were buying Jiyanama's gift, so I'd say your disguise is pretty perfect~
Tindoiimu: Hmm... maybe...
Tingko: So, we've got Jiyanama her Hanazono Chiyuki autographed portrait. We should probably pick up some essentials, too.
Tindoiimu: Ugh... more shopping...
Hutchinson: Come one, come all! Morgan's Marvelous Circus welcomes you!
Sophie: Ladies, gentlemen, boys and girls! Good afternoon!
Sophie: We are Morgan's Marvelous Circus! Bringers of smilers, purveyors of joy!
Hurried Turtle: Circus? What the heck...?
Tingko: Morgan's Marvelous Circus? Never heard of 'em...
Sophie: Our performance is about to begin! Please everyone, stick around and feast your eyes!
Tindoiimu: That's a human, right? And a whale, and a demi-human...
Tingko: Prince—I mean, Sir.
Tingko: Let's watch! We've got some time until we have to go back, anyway.
Tindoiimu: I had a feeling you'd say that...
Tindoiimu: To be honest I'm quite curious about this 'circus' myself.
Sophie: (...Not too many people... No worries! We'll just drum up some hype...!)
Sophie: Now, first up---
Sophie: With his legendary, one-hundred percent genuine, one-hundred percent gigantic antlers, please welcome the one-and-only... Hutchinson!
Old Beast: Wow, those antlers sure are huge!
Passer-by: That's not normal! They're too huge!
Tindoiimu: ......
Sophie: And next onto the stage, we have—
Sophie: The hedgiest hedgehog in the business—Hanbei!
Older Jackal: Eh, does that hedgehog have no spikes?
Younger Jackal: I mean, am I seeing things or something? How can there be a spike-less hedgehog?
Sophie: Now, the final act you've all been waiting for!
Sophie: You're about to have a whale of a time—It's Ru-yi!!
Ru-yi: Sophie!!
Older Jackal: Booo! Get off the stage!!
Younger Jackal: No one wants to see this blubbery freak! Get her outta here!
Ru-yi: Mm... mmm...
Sophie: Ru-yi, it's okay!
Sophie: Please, get a load of Ru-yi's magnificent blowhole!!
Sophie: And that's all for today's performance! Thank you for watching! We're Morgan's Marvelous Circus, and we hope we made your day brighter!
Sophie: No need for donations~ We only ask for a smile!
Tindoiimu: Tingko, we still have some money left after buying Jiyanama's gift, right?
Tingko: Yep.
Sophie: Thank you so much! Please come see us again!
Tindoiimu: We enjoyed your performance very much.
Tingko: Keep at it~!
Tingko: Well, seems like we've got everything we need.
Tindoiimu: Let's head back.
Hutchinson: Hello, Sir! I'm with Morgan's Marvelous Circus! This flyer lists all the times for all our future performances! Hope to see you there!!

Tingko: Their performances are actually really great! But... 
When I see them, I can't help but thinking of the Insect Tribe...
Tingko: You know what I mean, Prin—I mean, Sir?
Tindoiimu: Yeah... the east isn't very welcoming to outsiders. Even that little girl... the way she was heckled like that...
Tindoiimu: But she kept on performing, smiling the whole time...
Tingko: She's a professional, I guess. That's the life she's signed up for... As long as we can keep coming out and seeing them perform, I'm happy~!
Older Jackal: Hey, didn't we tell you freaks to get out of here!?

Younger Jackal: You outsiders never seem to listen~
What makes you all think you could even come here in the first place!?
Hutchinson: We applied with the proper qilin authorities and received a performers permit just like we were suppo—
Older Jackal: Permit schmermit! This is our troupe's territory, and you're here tryin' to steal our business!
Younger Jackal: Not like anyone wants to watch yer stinkin' circus anyway!
Younger Jackal: Yer half-baked prancin and dancin' doesn't hold a candle to us! We've been hustling and practicing for over ten hard years!
Tindoiimu: (I'm a hostage... I really shouldn't get involved... but...)
Tingko: Sir, I... we...
Tindoiimu: (Oh yeah, my disguise! I can't be found out!)
Older Jackal: Who the...!?
Tindoiimu: Give it a rest.
Older Jackal: Hmph, damn human, quit stickin' yer nose in our business!
Younger Jackal: Guess I shouldn't be surprised you humans would stick up for a dumb demi-human.
Older Jackal: Still, I feel like I've got to teach you third-rate freaks a lesson, or else you'll go on ruining our reputation.
Tindoiimu: (Damn... I won't be able to do much more with my disguise like this.)
Younger Jackal: B-Big bro, this kid's got some tricks up his sleeve...
Older Jackal: Hmph, whatever. I'm not done yet! I'm not letting some demi-human get away with this!
Tindoiimu: —Stop!
